author: dlr
msg: A follow-up to r26841 (for issue #2880), changing 'svn commit
--changelist=not-found' to issue a hard error (rather than a warning),
for consistency with all other commands.
* subversion/svn/commit-cmd.c
(svn_cl__commit): If the specified changelist is not found, return a
hard error in the same style as other commands.
* subversion/tests/cmdline/commit_tests.py
(no_such_changelist): Expect an error (on stderr) instead of a
warning (on stdout).
Found by: epg
